This Women’s Day, Cosmopolitan India puts the spotlight on five women who don’t just ‘want it all’ but have ‘got it all’. Are they pretty? Indeed. But what makes them a class apart is that they are unstoppable, and they show other women what it’s like to be groundbreaking, sensational, inspirational, fearless…and ICONIC.

In a world riddled with uncertainty, commercial airline pilot and Covid-19 frontline worker, Laxmi Shailesh Joshi (@pilotlaxmi); actor, philanthropist and Padma Shri awardee, Raveena Tandon (@officialraveenatandon); digital content creator and former RJ, Karishma Gangwal (@rjkarishma); fashion and beauty content creator, Aastha Shah (@aasthashah97); Indian badminton player and two-time Olympic medallist, PV Sindhu (@pvsindhu1) are forces in their own right—women who defy all odds.
Want to take a cue and (also) make a difference? Well, no better time than now to celebrate that one trait, which makes you stand out.

Choose yourself and opt to be #MoreThanPretty with @mango @mangostores_india

latestPosts.caption:
Recap of 2024! Extremely grateful♥️🧿

1. Walked the red carpet at the Cannes Film Festival for the first time.
2. Achieved one of my milestones of one million followers. 
3. My most viral video with @a.magic.man shot in USA. 
4. Took my parents abroad after 10 years.
5. Worked with my dream brand @bvlgari 
6. Visited Brazil with @primevideo for the launch of Your Fault movie. 
7. Gifted my mom a luxury purse from @gucci (my first ever expensive buy had to be for my mom)
8. Attended the ARWedding.
9. On the Cosmopolitan Magazine cover along side such talented personalities. 
10. Had a cute moment with my crush. 
11. This year’s best look I wore at Cannes
12. Won two awards, one from @ndtv and the second at @exhibitmagazine 
13. Surprised dad and took him to Dubai for his favourite singer’s concert 
14. Celebrated World Vitiligo Day, embracing my skin every single day.
15. Traveled in business class for the first time @emirates 
16. Wore @snbyshantanunikhil at the fashion week.
17. Collaborated with my favourite beauty brand @lancomeofficial 
18. Visited Singapore with @disney for the launch of their cruise dressed as Elsa. 
19. Started a new YT channel named Couple Uncouple with @thakkarjigar111 
20. I cannot take pictures of me crying, but the last photo means that every day is not a good day. Everything shown on the internet is probably the good side but everyone has their bad days too. Multiple breakdowns, creative blocks, not achieving milestones, etc, it is completely okay to not be okay.

Thank you to each one of you for being a part of 2024!

2025 I am coming for you✨

Elegance in a bottle of @bvlgari🦢 

Shot and edited by @ziaulhaque
